The final version/release of this map I'm going to do. Every single visual flaw and error I could find has been fixed. I've added soundscapes, a 3D skybox, and a few other details.

Just copy the map .bsp and its .nav into the 'cstrike/maps' folder and you should be up and running. If you have a missing texture, copy the included texture files into the 'cstrike/materials' folder. If there is no ambient sound, your going to need to put the scripts in the 'cstrike/scripts' folder. Create this if you don't already have one in the 'cstrike' folder.

This is a map I made to get back into mapping.

I haven't made a "real" map for almost a year now, and clearing off the cobwebs was nice.

This is a map I made for AwpaholicA.com's GunGame server (found here 72.249.94.82:27015), which is my kind of spin-off of funtimes.

I really like the sizing and game play of funtimes, however I believed that the top wasn't being utilized enough. I wanted it to be, so I made it easier accessible. Hover something I didn't take into account, was how fast the game play would go now that players are able to both advance and fight for the high ground.

Even though AwpaholicA.com's servers hold picky regulars, this became a popular map, and is now played consistently.

it has 32 spawns, and is a great map for quick games.


--Thank you AwpaholicA.com--

ENJOY! AND PLEASE GIVE FEEDBACK!!!!

Gg_austere_facility By: Natalya[AF] Map Features: - 48 Spawns - Cubemaps - Radar Map - Custom Textures This is my first attempt at a Gun Game map. It has a rather simple layout, 2 spawns on either side of the map connected by a tunnel. The tunnel has 2 stairs leading into the main part of the map. The main bit is the interior of a warehouse type building, presumably underground. It has 2 main levels. The second level can be accessed by 2 stairways, each of which is near a spawn. The textures are the skybox (look up in the main area to see stars) and a counter top in the tunnel area. It also has built in some skins for various props including the vending machines, van, pickup truck, and some other small stuff in the tunnels. The skins shouldn't show up on other maps and won't override any customs you have when you go to another map so don't worry about that happening. They will show up here only. Inspiration came from this map: gg_underground_z But all the work in my map is 100% mine and original. I didn't actually take anything out of underground z aside from ideas. Thanks to Seraphim for helping error test it. Anyway... I hope y'all enjoy the map. Expect a Death Match version tomorrow. *EDIT* Here's that Death Match version: dm_austere_facility

This map is more or less my first serious project.
My girlfriend came up with the idea when I asked her about some interesting mapping or gaming scenarios. "A concentration camp would be kinda unique." she said and that's when I started working. After 3-4 Months of work I proudly can say that gg_auschwitz reached Beta status (its not a final because none except me and some close friends tested it yet).

The gameplay is pretty fast, there are 4 different ways that allow the players to enter all areas of the map very quickly. The balance has been referred to as "good one" , but I hope I get some good bug/issue reports to get everything perfectly. I made the map this dark on purpose, its a concept map that should mirror the vicious things that went on for years on that specific place.

Final note: 
With this map I do not want to express any kind of racist or any political opinion. I simply wanted to sort historical things out for myself by means of building it for everyone to access and experience, so that maybe the attention is drawn again on the subject of WW2. Awareness is the best thing to evade future mistakes concerning the topic of racism.

I just love the map cs_assault, but I much prefer to play GG, so i though I should make an version of assault for it. This is my second released map, and if you look at my other one you can see the improvement as I have just been playing with hammer for about a year, really getting to grips with it with out releasing pointless unfinished dev textured full bright maps. That's another thing I hate about GG maps, most people put no time into them, and I am sick of Dev Textures. This was a big project for me, taking just over a month and I really like the result. I want to give out a big thank you to Cheebs as he offered to test my map out before I released it and look for errors and things that could be improved and did a great job of it. Lots of respect for him. If anybody puts this map into rotation on there GG server, please let me know as I would love to play it with you guys. Another thing, If you guys find any more errors let me know and I will fix them, this is only in beta stage. In the final version I am going to try and add a Radar Image.
*** Please Download and Rate! Looking for lots of feedback, so I can improve the map and my skills! ***
